Data were analysed using IBM SPSS Statistics for Windows, version 22.0 (IBM Corp., Armonk, NY, USA). The crude analyses were performed to determine the association of DENV seropositivity (both recent and past infection) with sociodemographic factors, comorbidities, and a past family history of dengue. Variables with a 
 P-value <0.20 derived in the crude analysis were included in the final adjusted, binary logistic regression model; 
 P-value <0.05 was considered statistically significant.
